node.text: Abortions won’t end. Safe abortions just did, in Texas. Until women are seen as more than just mothers and caretakers, until they actually care about children once they are born, until women are supported in the work place, until women’s healthcare is not politicized, until women are treated fairly and equally in every way, the fight continues.

node.text: “TX Republicans think masks and vaccines violate their right to control their bodies, but allowing anyone to sue an Uber driver for taking a woman, 7 weeks pregnant, after being raped, to get an abortion…..that’s legal.” I stand with a women’s right to choose. Today and everyday. Texas GOP, you are trash. Today and everyday.

node.text: I have a injury I’m working through but not moving is not an option. I’m using cryo and ice baths, hyperbaric therapy, (thank god for @remedyplace), my @hyperice equipment, my treatments @kinetix365 (thank you Tarek), eating clean and of course, my sessions with my best friend and trainer,  @paolomascitti . Working out is my happy place. Clears my head. Keeps me focused. 👊🏾 🎶 by @methodmanofficial and @redmangilla

I’ve teamed up with @votedotorg to remind California that we have an incredibly important recall election on September 14th. The LAST day to register is Monday August 30th. Head to the link in my bio for everything you need. Text at least 10 friends and remind them. Help get them registered. We need the same energy we had in November! #vote 🗳

node.text: I don’t run for a pill or medicine at the onset of a cold or headache. I rarely get those. I eat plant based. I workout. I practice homeopathy. I practice integrated wellness but even I know, I needed to do my part, take my family, friends and community’s well being into account, and get vaccinated. As COVID cases surge again, it’s more important than ever to do your part. It starts with being vaccinated, but it doesn’t stop there. I'm joining the @phenomenal PRO-VAXXER campaign in partnership with @higherheights4 to encourage you to share your story — research shows that sharing personal stories of being vaccinated is a key influence in driving up community vaccination rates. This isn’t just about protecting yourself, it’s about all of us. It’s about taking action and showing leadership. So, what's your story? Let me know in the comments, and click the link in bio to get the tee.

node.text: Perhaps my last #carelikeademon initiative. Seeing the devastation left behind in Afghanistan has broken my heart. @vitalvoices have expanded their initiatives to support Afghan women on the front lines.  This was our Season 6 wrap gift. You can’t buy this anywhere. A hoodie in medium/large. Sandals in medium/large. Towel. Lucifer beach chair. I will sign them and send to one lucky person who contributes to this fundraiser. Please provide proof in DMs. The next 48 hours are crucial. 🇦🇫🚨#afghanistan #vitalvoices #carelikeademon
